I chose the death as the worse outcome.  Locations were equal to me. If it was the exact same scenario but different places, neither of them was worse. In most cases I said both were equally bad because the same number of people were being killed. Where the event took place had no impact on my decisions.

There were certain questions that I viewed as obvious, such as $1,000 in damages or $200 in damages, or a car being hurt or dying.
